DataElement.preferredName: Protocol Agent Transfer Administration Performed Study Activity Variance Reason ISO21090.ST.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The completed action in which an authorized party at a designated study site dispenses or receives a study agent to/from a study subject. EXAMPLE(S): StudySubject receives a bottle of pills. A description of the variance of an administrative activity. EXAMPLE(S): Early or late occurrence of an activity, such as early withdrawal from study. Higher/lower amount of a transfer, such as transfer of less study agent than planned.
